07a03a8a-2b5a-4b8b-aeeb-eab1ba16e2a6.do_description: To make the output, you have to... put center box color in 1x1, outside box color in 3x3, then 5x5, then 7x7 and so on
07a03a8a-2b5a-4b8b-aeeb-eab1ba16e2a6.grid_description: The output grid size...if 2 color 3x3, if 3 color 5x5, if 4 color 7x7
07a03a8a-2b5a-4b8b-aeeb-eab1ba16e2a6.see_description: In the input, you should see... grid with 2 or more colors

439d0d02-e1bb-4228-91f6-3d29e878d1c1.do_description: To make the output, you have to...the color all the way inside is 1x1 in the center. the next color is 3x3 in the center (other than the 1x1 from before). If you have a third color, the center 5x5 is that and finally the 4th color is the far 7x7 edge.
439d0d02-e1bb-4228-91f6-3d29e878d1c1.grid_description: The output grid size...if 2 color 3x3, if 3 color 5x5 if 4 color 7x7
439d0d02-e1bb-4228-91f6-3d29e878d1c1.see_description: In the input, you should see... one color inside another. you might have a third or 4th color .

87f0b699-c0d1-412a-8e56-e086b27371a4.do_description: To make the output, you have to...Identify the color using the least number of squares as your central color in the output.  Follow with second color, then third and final colors.
87f0b699-c0d1-412a-8e56-e086b27371a4.grid_description: The output grid size...4 colors is 7x7 squares; 2 colors is 3x3 squares, 3 colors is 5x5 squares
87f0b699-c0d1-412a-8e56-e086b27371a4.see_description: In the input, you should see...2, 3, and 4 color patterns

f1122852-9d4f-4f6a-9cd8-fdc30b8f9d10.do_description: To make the output, you have to...color the outside border the same color as the outside border of the input grid. Continue to color the output grid using the next color until it is filled
f1122852-9d4f-4f6a-9cd8-fdc30b8f9d10.grid_description: The output grid size...is 2 times the number of colors - 1 (for example if there are 2 colors, the size is 3x3 (2 times 2 = 4 - 1 = 3)
f1122852-9d4f-4f6a-9cd8-fdc30b8f9d10.see_description: In the input, you should see...a large grid with two or more colors
